Package org.jfree.data.time

Interfaces and classes for time-related data.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TimePeriod
    A period of time measured to millisecond precision using two instances of java.util.Date.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DateRange
    A range specified in terms of two java.util.Date objects.
    DateRangeTest
    Some tests for the DateRange class.
    Day
    Represents a single day in the range 1-Jan-1900 to 31-Dec-9999.
    DayTest
    Tests for the Day class.
    DynamicTimeSeriesCollection
    A dynamic dataset.
    FixedMillisecond
    Wrapper for a java.util.Date object that allows it to be used as a RegularTimePeriod.
    FixedMillisecondTest
    Tests for the FixedMillisecond class.
    Hour
    Represents an hour in a specific day.
    HourTest
    Tests for the Hour class.
    Millisecond
    Represents a millisecond.
    MillisecondTest
    Tests for the Millisecond class.
    Minute
    Represents a minute.
    MinuteTest
    Tests for the Minute class.
    Month
    Represents a single month.
    MonthTest
    Tests for the Month class.
    MovingAverage
    A utility class for calculating moving averages of time series data.
    MovingAverageTest
    Tests for the MovingAverage class.
    Quarter
    Defines a quarter (in a given year).
    QuarterTest
    Tests for the {link Quarter} class.
    RegularTimePeriod
    An abstract class representing a unit of time.
    Second
    Represents a second in a particular day.
    SecondTest
    Tests for the Second class.
    SimpleTimePeriod
    An arbitrary period of time, measured to millisecond precision using java.util.Date.
    SimpleTimePeriodTest
    Tests for the SimpleTimePeriod class.
    TimePeriodAnchor
    Used to indicate one of three positions in a time period: START, MIDDLE and END.
    TimePeriodAnchorTest
    Tests for the TimePeriodAnchor class.
    TimePeriodValue
    Represents a time period and an associated value.
    TimePeriodValues
    A structure containing zero, one or many TimePeriodValue instances.
    TimePeriodValuesCollection
    A collection of TimePeriodValues objects.
    TimePeriodValuesCollectionTest
    Some tests for the TimePeriodValuesCollection class.
    TimePeriodValuesTest
    A collection of test cases for the TimePeriodValues class.
    TimePeriodValuesTest.MySeriesChangeListener
    A listener used for detecting series change events.
    TimePeriodValueTest
    Tests for the TimePeriodValue class.
    TimeSeries
    Represents a sequence of zero or more data items in the form (period, value) where 'period' is some instance of a subclass of RegularTimePeriod.
    TimeSeriesCollection
    A collection of time series objects.
    TimeSeriesCollectionTest
    A collection of test cases for the TimeSeriesCollection class.
    TimeSeriesDataItem
    Represents one data item in a time series.
    TimeSeriesDataItemTest
    Tests for the TimeSeriesDataItem class.
    TimeSeriesTableModel
    Wrapper around a time series to convert it to a table model for use in a JTable.
    TimeSeriesTest
    A collection of test cases for the TimeSeries class.
    TimeTableXYDataset
    A dataset for regular time periods that implements the TableXYDataset interface.
    TimeTableXYDatasetTest
    A collection of test cases for the TimeTableXYDataset class.
    Week
    A calendar week.
    WeekTest
    Tests for the Week class.
    Year
    Represents a year in the range -9999 to 9999.
    YearTest
    Tests for the Year class.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    TimePeriodFormatException
    An exception that indicates an invalid format in a string representing a time period.
